### Discussed in https://github.com/tailwindlabs/tailwindcss/discussions/13547

<div type='discussions-op-text'>

<sup>Originally posted by **sxdav** April 18, 2024</sup>
I'm trying to add css vars aliases to the config like that:

`const config: Config = {
  theme: {
    colors: {
      '-bg-primary': 'var(--bg-primary)'
    }
  }
}`

Idea is to use them as `bg--bg-primary`, similar to css vars syntax. But tailwind generates a `-bg-bg-primary` class which contains `background-color: var(--bg-primary);`, instead of `bg--bg-primary` which does not seems like an expected behavior.</div>
